This paper discusses the use of morphosyntactic lexicons and word vector representations for improving the accuracy of statistical part-of-speech taggers. This topic falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also compares the performances of different systems, including feature-based and neural-based models, which involves machine learning techniques. Therefore, it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of external lexical information, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper covers multilingual part-of-speech tagging, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
